1
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,800
英国国王亨利五世和法国国王查尔斯六世

2
00:00:40,850 --> 00:00:41,920
于1420年签订了特鲁瓦条约

3
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:44,920
条约规定法国附属于英国 直至国王死去

4
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:48,920
随后两个国王相继死去

5
00:00:48,920 --> 00:00:52,920
年仅几个月的亨利六世 成为了英格兰及法兰西的国王

6
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:54,200
查尔斯七世 法兰西皇太子

7
00:00:54,250 --> 00:00:55,920
则不情愿把国家交给一个小孩或是他老师贝德福德公爵手中

8
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:59,920
一场血战在所难免 英国随同勃艮第人开始侵略法国

9
00:01:14,920 --> 00:01:17,920
罗亚尔河 这道天然屏障 暂时挡住了侵略者

10
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:22,920
查尔斯七世避难于希农 他渴望到兰斯去加冕为法国国王

11
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:25,920
可是兰斯正在英国人的手中

12
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,920
法国正在经历历史上最黑暗的时期

13
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,920
能拯救法国的只有

14
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,920
奇迹

15
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:40,920
是谁?
Is anybody there?

16
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:44,060
贞德
Jeanne.

17
00:01:47,430 --> 00:01:51,630
见到你我很高兴 可是你一天来两三次...
I'm always happy to see you, but to keep coming twice, three times a day...

18
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:54,770
 我要忏悔  可你早晨已经忏悔过了
 I need to confess.  You already confessed this morning.

19
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,640
我要再忏悔一次
I need to confess again.

20
00:01:56,710 --> 00:02:00,110
什么样的罪孽...
What terrible sin have you committed since then...

21
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:02,840
让你一天都无法等待?
that can't wait till tomorrow to be forgiven?

22
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:06,850
我看见一个修道士没穿鞋 就给了他几双
I saw a poor monk without shoes, so I gave him some.

23
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,890
施舍是没有罪过的 贞德
There's no sin in charity,Jeanne.

24
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:12,450
 可那些鞋不是我的  那是谁的?
 They weren't my shoes.  Whose were they?

25
00:02:12,530 --> 00:02:15,790
 是我爸爸的  我相信他会原谅你的
 My father's.  I'm sure he'll forgive you.

26
00:02:15,860 --> 00:02:17,990
他已经原谅我了
He already did.

27
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:20,000
但我希望耶稣也能原谅我
But I wantJesus to forgive me too.

28
00:02:20,070 --> 00:02:23,590
如果一直祈求宽恕罪过
If we were to ask forgiveness all the time...

29
00:02:23,670 --> 00:02:25,600
那就要在教堂呆一辈子了
we'd spend our whole life in church.

30
00:02:25,670 --> 00:02:29,070
 那样不好吗?  不是不好 只是...
 Is that bad?  Well, no, but...

31
00:02:31,650 --> 00:02:34,770
 你在家快乐吗?  是的 很快乐
 Are you happy at home?  Oh, yes, very.

32
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:37,150
你母亲呢? 她好吗?
And your mother? Everything's fine with her?

33
00:02:37,220 --> 00:02:39,690
是 她好极了
Yes, she's wonderful.

34
00:02:39,750 --> 00:02:42,810
那你姐姐凯瑟琳呢 还一直是你的好朋友吗?
And your sister, Catherine, she's still your best friend?

35
00:02:42,890 --> 00:02:46,850
我姐姐...好极了
My sister's just...She's wonderful.

36
00:02:46,930 --> 00:02:50,830
那你其他的朋友呢? 你常跟他们一起玩吗?
And what about your other friends? You don't like playing with them?

37
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:53,830
是的 我们常在一起玩
Oh, yes. I play with them, lots.

38
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:57,800
那一切都好极了
Everything sounds wonderful.

39
00:02:57,870 --> 00:03:00,600
是的
Yes, it is.

40
00:03:00,670 --> 00:03:02,370
那你为什么还总是来这里呢?
Then why are you here so often?

41
00:03:03,980 --> 00:03:07,380
我在这里感到安全 在这里我可以跟他说话
I feel safe here. It's where I can talk to him.

42
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:10,940
他?
Him?

43
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:14,750
我也想跟他说几句...
Well, I try to talk to him...

44
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:18,550
可大部分时候都是他一个人在说
but mostly he's the one who does the talking.

45
00:03:18,630 --> 00:03:22,390
这个"他"是谁?
Who is this "he"?

46
00:03:23,660 --> 00:03:27,030
他没说过他的名字
He never says his name.

47
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:30,900
那他...
What does he...

48
00:03:30,970 --> 00:03:32,870
长什么样子?
look like?

49
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,170
漂亮极了
Beautiful.

50
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:46,650
他都跟你说些什么?
What does he say to you?

51
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,380
他说...
He says...

52
00:03:53,390 --> 00:03:57,800
他说我要做个好人...
He says...He says I must be good...

53
00:03:57,860 --> 00:04:01,890
多帮助他人 照顾好自己
and help everyone and take care of myself.

54
00:04:03,270 --> 00:04:05,200
你说他是从天上来的吗?
Do you think he's coming from the sky?

55
00:04:07,510 --> 00:04:09,100
可能吧
Perhaps.

56
00:04:10,580 --> 00:04:14,840
可不管他是哪里来 我觉得听他的没错...
But wherever he's coming from, I think you should listen to him...

57
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:18,580
那确实是个好建议
'cause it sounds like he's giving you very good advice.

58
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:46,540
真是 真是好极了!
It's...It's wonderful!

59
00:04:47,950 --> 00:04:49,470
真是好极了
It's wonderful.

60
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:08,620
贞德
Jeanne.

61
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:14,930
妈妈!
Mother!

62
00:10:21,010 --> 00:10:22,450
凯瑟琳!
Catherine!

63
00:10:34,990 --> 00:10:37,290
贞德 你还好吧? 他们没伤到你吧?
Jeanne, are you all right? Did they hurt you?

64
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:39,130
我很好
I'm fine, really.

65
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:42,730
我们一直在找你 现在到处都是英国人
We've all been looking for you. The English are everywhere.

66
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,770
 我去教堂了  是吗?
 I was in the church.  Really?

67
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:47,240
我去找牧师了 你知道他对我说什么吗?
I was talking to the priest. Do you know what he said to me?

68
00:10:47,310 --> 00:10:49,240
烧掉那里!
Burn over there!

69
00:10:49,310 --> 00:10:51,780
以后再说吧 快藏进来
Tell me later. Quick, hide in here.

70
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:56,010
 那你去哪里?  我就在这里 哪儿也不去
 Where are you gonna be?  I'll be right here.

71
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,670
我保证
I promise.

72
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:06,860
噢 那就是我说的战利品了
Well, that's what I call booty.

73
00:11:44,530 --> 00:11:46,020
伙计
Comrade.

74
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:03,310
这女人还有把剑
A woman with a sword.

75
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:08,050
你们看
Look at this.

76
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,990
法国男人真是孬种 居然让女人去打仗
Frenchmen are such cowards, they've left all the fightin' to women.

77
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:15,020
如果那是上帝的意愿 那就没错的
If that's God's will, then so be it.

78
00:12:15,090 --> 00:12:18,890
那正和我口味 我喜欢女人
Fine with me. I love women.

79
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,910
别动 臭婊子
Hold still, bitch.

80
00:12:43,990 --> 00:12:46,250
你扭来扭去我怎么办事儿?
How can I do it if you keep wriggling about?

81
00:13:38,010 --> 00:13:39,340
轮到你们了
Your turn now.

82
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:15,210
主啊 保佑这些逝者的灵魂吧
God, preserve and bless the soul of this, our dearly departed.

83
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:18,720
并让我们远离恐惧和罪恶 阿门
Keep us safe from fear and sin. Amen.

84
00:14:25,460 --> 00:14:26,620
开始吧
Come on.

85
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,900
听我说 贞德
Listen,Jeanne.

86
00:15:07,970 --> 00:15:12,670
你姨妈要带你去她家住几星期
Your aunt and uncle are gonna take you to their house for a couple of weeks...

87
00:15:12,740 --> 00:15:15,710
好让我们重建这里
just to give us time to rebuild things here.

88
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:25,440
明白了吗?
You understand?

89
00:16:34,990 --> 00:16:37,650
上帝 感谢您赐予我们食物
Lord, we give thanks for the food you've given us.

90
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,660
教会我们热爱自己的家园
Teach us always to love this land...

91
00:16:39,730 --> 00:16:42,630
并保护它不受坏人的破坏
and to save it from those who seek to destroy it.

92
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,290
 阿门  阿门
 Amen.  Amen.

93
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:09,480
晚安
So, good night, then.

94
00:17:16,530 --> 00:17:20,860
 她以后会怎么样呢?  她会没事的
 What's going to happen to her?  She'll be fine.

95
00:17:20,930 --> 00:17:25,370
慢慢长大 嫁个好人 生几个孩子 你就别担心了
She'll grow up, find a good man, make him some children. Don't worry.

96
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,170
她是受过伤害 可她活过来了
She's been hurt, but she'll survive.

97
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:30,230
明天她就会一切顺利了
Tomorrow she'll be as right as rain.

98
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:32,540
你等着看吧
You'll see.

99
00:17:36,620 --> 00:17:38,550
我要见牧师
I want to see a priest.

100
00:18:01,370 --> 00:18:05,570
 为什么非要她去死?  这只有上帝能回答
 Why did she have to die?  Only God can answer that.

101
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:09,210
我知道耶稣说要爱你的敌人 可我做不到
I know Jesus says to love your enemies, but I can't.

102
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:13,410
我盼着那些英国佬 在地狱受尽煎熬 永不翻身!
I just want the English to burn in hell forever and ever!

103
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:16,980
我知道你很愤怒 贞德
I realize your anger,Jeanne.

104
00:18:17,060 --> 00:18:19,580
可我们必须学会宽恕 它是很难...
But we must learn to forgive. It's hard...

105
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:23,360
但报仇是不会带来和平的
but revenge will never bring about peace.

106
00:18:23,430 --> 00:18:26,020
那什么可以呢? 怎样做她才能回来呢?
What will? And what will bring her back?

107
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:30,000
为什么先死的人是她而不是我?
And why did she have to die in the first place instead of me?

108
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:32,700
他为什么不要我的生命而要她的?
Why didn't He take my life instead of hers?

109
00:18:32,770 --> 00:18:35,370
都是我的错! 是我回来晚了!
It was my fault! I was late!

110
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:39,940
她把自己的藏身地方给了我! 可他为什么要救我呢?
She gave me her hiding place! Why did He save me?

111
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:43,110
冷静些 贞德 冷静些
Calm down,Jeanne. Calm down.

112
00:18:46,020 --> 00:18:49,320
我不会假装了解上帝的意愿...
I don't pretend to know God's will...

113
00:18:49,390 --> 00:18:52,220
可有一点我确信不疑
but one thing I am sure:

114
00:18:52,290 --> 00:18:56,490
上帝这么做自会有他的理由
The Lord always has a good reason.

115
00:18:56,560 --> 00:18:59,960
他选择你可能是因为他需要你
Perhaps He chose you because He needs you...

116
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:02,760
为了某种更高的感召
for some higher calling.

117
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:05,700
只要你响应了那感召...
As long as you answer that call...

118
00:19:05,770 --> 00:19:09,570
你姐姐的死就不会是毫无价值的了
your sister will not have died in vain.

119
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:12,110
我不想等他的召唤
I don't want to wait for His call.

120
00:19:12,180 --> 00:19:14,110
耐心些
Be patient.

121
00:19:14,180 --> 00:19:16,670
我要一直与他同在
I want to be with Him always.

122
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:20,240
你会一直与他同在的
Soon you will be able to take part in your Holy Mass.

123
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:23,620
等你可以领圣餐时...
When you eat of His flesh and drink of His blood...

124
00:19:23,690 --> 00:19:25,680
你就将与他同在
you will be at one with Him.

125
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:29,850
我现在就要
I want to be at one with Him now.

126
00:19:35,700 --> 00:19:37,830
牧师他说什么?
So, what did he say?

127
00:19:37,900 --> 00:19:40,800
他说不管她何时想来教堂 我们就要带她过来
He says we must bring her to church whenever she wants.

128
00:19:40,870 --> 00:19:44,240
他说的容易 反正又不是他来接送
Easy for him. He's not the one who has to do the bringing.

129
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:46,440
别这么说 这很重要的
Come on. This is important.

130
00:19:46,510 --> 00:19:49,710
我们不能让她离开我们的视线
We mustn't let her out of our sight.

131
00:19:49,780 --> 00:19:53,680
别担心 我会像看自己的影子一样看着她
Don't worry. I will watch her like my own shadow.

132
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:45,600
我现在就要与你同在
I want to be at one with You now.

133
00:21:17,140 --> 00:21:19,600
给法国皇太子的信
A message for the dauphin of France.

134
00:21:29,110 --> 00:21:30,740
给皇太子殿下的信
A message.

135
00:21:40,290 --> 00:21:42,920
队长 这是给皇太子殿下的信
Captain, a message for the dauphin.

136
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,400
放那里吧
I'll take it.

137
00:21:51,970 --> 00:21:54,130
皇太子殿下! 皇太子殿下!
The dauphin! The dauphin!

138
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:12,690
路易斯 怎么没去上课?
Louis. Louis. Hey. Shouldn't you be learning your lessons?

139
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,820
我不想上课 我想学搏击
I don't want to learn. I want to fight.

140
00:22:14,890 --> 00:22:18,800
那个你以后会学的 现在还是先学学擦鼻子吧
You will. But for now, you must at least learn to wipe your nose.

141
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:24,530
有殿下的信
A letter for His Majesty.

142
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:33,710
又是那自称是洛林处女的人寄来的
Another one from this girl calling herself the Maiden of Lorraine.

143
00:22:33,780 --> 00:22:35,970
我自己不会读么?
I can read for myself, you know?

144
00:22:36,050 --> 00:22:39,640
她说她是上帝派来的 真是吹牛
She pretends she's been sent by God. Charlatans.

145
00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:41,850
没能把她们全都烧死 真是太可惜了
It's a pity there isn't enough wood to burn them all.

146
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:44,820
 她说她明天就到这里了  殿下 您不能见她
 She says she'll be here tomorrow.  You mustn't see her, My Lord.

147
00:22:44,890 --> 00:22:48,520
您根本不了解她 甚至不知道她是不是从洛林来的
We know nothing about her. We don't even know if she's from Lorraine.

148
00:22:48,590 --> 00:22:50,820
她从哪里来很重要吗?
What difference does it make where she comes from?

149
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,960
如果她是从勃艮第来的 那就不一样了
If she comes from Burgundy, it makes a difference.

150
00:22:53,030 --> 00:22:55,590
这可能是个圈套 您看 署名为"X"
It might be a trap. Look, signed "X."

151
00:22:55,670 --> 00:22:57,160
"X"算是个什么名字呢?
What sort of a name is "X"?

152
00:22:57,240 --> 00:23:00,430
莫非上帝的使者连自己的名字都不会写?
Or must we assume that a messenger of God can't even write her own name?

153
00:23:00,510 --> 00:23:03,770
殿下 特利莫伊说的很对 她还说她能听见主的声音
My Lord, Tremoille is correct. She says she hears voices.

154
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:06,240
她可能是个女巫 一个巫婆
She may be a sorceress, a witch.

155
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:09,580
勒诺尔 在你眼里谁都是巫师
Regnault, you see witches everywhere.

156
00:23:09,650 --> 00:23:11,840
她只是个农民罢了
She's just a peasant.

157
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:15,220
一个关心国王的农民
A peasant who cares about her king.

158
00:23:15,290 --> 00:23:19,590
她想要我加冕为王 然后为我而战
All she wants is to see me crowned and permission to fight for me.

159
00:23:19,660 --> 00:23:23,490
不只是这样 她要您给她一支军队 军费您出
Not exactly. She wants you to give her an army at your expense.

160
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:26,790
记住您母亲已经把国库花了个精光了
Bearing in mind your mother stole every last piece of gold in the treasury...

161
00:23:26,870 --> 00:23:29,100
您是冒不起这个险的
I fail to see how you can afford such an adventure.

162
00:23:29,170 --> 00:23:31,100
愿意的话我会见她的
I can see her if I want to.

163
00:23:35,110 --> 00:23:37,800
一半的法国都落到英国人手里了
After all, with half of France in the hands of the English...

164
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:39,280
我还有什么好失去的?
what have I got to lose?

165
00:23:39,340 --> 00:23:40,440
另一半
The other half.

166
00:23:40,510 --> 00:23:42,880
殿下 您一定不能见她
You mustn't see her, Your Majesty.

167
00:23:42,950 --> 00:23:45,040
她可能是魔鬼派来的
She may be an instrument of the devil.

168
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:46,950
我倒认为你该见见
Well, I think you should.

169
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:55,790
这下有趣了
Well, here's an amusing situation.

170
00:23:55,860 --> 00:23:59,520
我深爱的母亲
I would love to know why my devoted mother in law thinks one thing...

171
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:02,930
跟两个我最信赖的顾问
and my two most loyal and trusted advisors...

