 Sire, are you... I'm fine.

356
00:43:42,860 --> 00:43:46,700
这位是吉恩·德奥兰 我最忠诚的朋友 最棒的射手
This is, in fact,Jean d'Aulon, my loyal friend and finest archer.

357
00:43:46,770 --> 00:43:49,000
你来负责照料她
I put her in your care.

358
00:43:49,070 --> 00:43:52,730
在城堡中给她找个合适的住处
Find her suitable lodgings here in the castle...

359
00:43:52,810 --> 00:43:54,780
守护她的安全
and guard her with your life.

360
00:43:54,840 --> 00:43:58,110
陛下 我不需要住处 我们要进军去奥尔良
Sire, I won't be needing any lodgings if we're to be marching on Orleans.

361
00:43:58,180 --> 00:44:00,240
奥尔良已经坚守了半年了...
Orleans has held out for six months...

362
00:44:00,310 --> 00:44:03,080
不急这两三天
so I don't suppose a few days more will make much difference.

363
00:44:03,150 --> 00:44:04,740
好好休息一下
Take some rest.

364
00:44:12,290 --> 00:44:14,020
把包放在这儿吧
Put the bags here.

365
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,530
请接受我的道歉...
Please accept my apologies...

366
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:21,030
我刚才假扮做...你明白的
for me pretending to be the...you know.

367
00:44:21,100 --> 00:44:23,040
我能喝点水吗?
Do you think that I can have some water?

368
00:44:23,100 --> 00:44:25,870
水 当然可以
Water. Yes, of course.

369
00:44:25,940 --> 00:44:27,870
你去弄些水来
Would you get some water?

370
00:44:27,940 --> 00:44:30,410
 还有其他的吗?  我要见牧师
 Anything else?  I need to see a priest.

371
00:44:30,480 --> 00:44:34,540
 现在?  是的 我今天还没有作忏悔
 Now?  Yes. I didn't confess today.

372
00:44:35,780 --> 00:44:39,810
好的 雷蒙德 去请牧师
All right. Raymond, a priest.

373
00:44:39,890 --> 00:44:40,880
还有其他的吗?
Anything else?

374
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:43,550
我还需要一匹新的战马...
I shall also be needing a new war horse...

375
00:44:43,620 --> 00:44:46,490
一把剑 盔甲...
a sword, armor...

376
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:49,090
再找位画家给我做面旗帜
and an artist to make a banner for me.

377
00:44:49,160 --> 00:44:52,000
 现在?  宜早不宜迟
 Now?  Better today than tomorrow.

378
00:44:52,070 --> 00:44:54,630
那可能要花些时间...
This might take a little time...

379
00:44:54,700 --> 00:44:58,330
我会尽力而为的
but let me see what I can do.

380
00:44:58,410 --> 00:45:02,340
还有 再找个能读会写的人来
Oh! I shall also be needing someone who can read and write.

381
00:45:02,410 --> 00:45:04,380
这个我就可以
This I can do.

382
00:45:04,450 --> 00:45:07,440
在英国人来之前 我一直在巴黎大学学习
I was studying at the University of Paris until the English invaded it.

383
00:45:07,520 --> 00:45:10,180
 我以为你是个弓箭手  是啊
 I thought you were an archer.  Yes, I am.

384
00:45:10,250 --> 00:45:14,850
我是个能读会写的弓箭手 您要写信给谁?
I'm an archer who can read and write. Who do you want to write to?

385
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,980
英国国王
The king of England.

386
00:45:19,060 --> 00:45:22,120
在我到奥尔良之前...
I want to give him the chance to leave in peace...

387
00:45:24,270 --> 00:45:27,430
给他一个和平撤军的机会
before I get to Orleans.

388
00:45:36,590 --> 00:45:40,500
主教和我刚开始 和勃根地人交涉
The archbishop and I have just begun negotiations with the Burgundians.

389
00:45:40,570 --> 00:45:42,260
如果能让他们站在我们这一边...
If we can bring them over to our side...

390
00:45:42,330 --> 00:45:46,060
当然要交涉 不过要有力量才能交涉
Negotiate, by all means, but from a position of strength.

391
00:45:46,140 --> 00:45:48,830
如果英军攻下奥尔良 就没有交涉的余地了
If the English take Orleans, there'll be nothing left to negotiate.

392
00:45:48,910 --> 00:45:50,840
其余国土将落入英军之手
The rest of the country will be theirs.

393
00:45:50,910 --> 00:45:53,780
夫人 这实在太愚蠢
My lady, it will be the height of folly...

394
00:45:53,850 --> 00:45:56,870
让这个孩子率领军队
to let this child lead our army...

395
00:45:56,950 --> 00:46:00,880
以国王的名义出兵 却没有验证她的真正动机
in the king's name without verifying her true motives.

396
00:46:00,950 --> 00:46:02,750
陛下 图洛伊是对的
My Lord, Tremoille is right.

397
00:46:02,850 --> 00:46:07,220
我们必须完全确定 她不是魔鬼的工具
We must be absolutely certain that she is not an instrument of the devil.

398
00:46:07,290 --> 00:46:11,230
这年头有什么事说得准?
How can anyone be absolutely certain about anything?

399
00:46:13,260 --> 00:46:16,700
有时候你该跟着直觉走
Sometimes our intuitions are our best counselors.

400
00:46:16,770 --> 00:46:20,900
在服从直觉之前必须听听教堂的说法
We must listen to Mother Holy Church before we listen to our intuitions.

401
00:46:27,210 --> 00:46:27,870
等等
Wait.

402
00:46:29,980 --> 00:46:33,180
她自称是处女
She claims to be a virgin.

403
00:46:33,250 --> 00:46:35,950
这个我们倒可以检查...
Well, that's something we can examine...

404
00:46:36,020 --> 00:46:39,390
也可以百分之百确定
and be absolutely certain about.

405
00:46:56,110 --> 00:46:58,630
那就查吧
Let's find out.

406
00:49:30,830 --> 00:49:33,160
如果她不是呢?
What if she's not?

407
00:49:33,230 --> 00:49:35,100
如果她不是...
If she's not...

408
00:49:35,300 --> 00:49:37,290
我就亲自杀了她
I'll kill her myself.

409
00:49:47,410 --> 00:49:51,070
没有堕落或奸淫的痕迹
There is no sign of corruption or violation.

410
00:49:51,150 --> 00:49:53,170
她是纯洁无瑕的
She is intact.

411
00:49:57,320 --> 00:50:01,550
你看到的形象 到底穿着什么衣服?
And what, exactly, was this vision wearing?

412
00:50:01,630 --> 00:50:03,150
我不记得了
I don't remember.

413
00:50:03,230 --> 00:50:06,030
这个形象有给你什么吗?
This vision, did it give you anything?

414
00:50:06,100 --> 00:50:08,960
一样东西? 戒子或念珠...
An object? A ring or a rosary...

415
00:50:09,070 --> 00:50:12,760
或任何证据 让我们可以相信你的话?
or anything by which we can verify your claim?

416
00:50:12,800 --> 00:50:14,600
他给我好的建议
He gave me good advice.

417
00:50:14,670 --> 00:50:18,130
你小时候有没有军事经验?
During your childhood, did you have any sort of military experience?

418
00:50:18,210 --> 00:50:19,200
没有
No.

419
00:50:19,510 --> 00:50:22,100
可曾学过剑术?
Are you practiced in the skills of swordsmanship?

420
00:50:22,180 --> 00:50:25,170
没有 但我很会耍棍
No, but I'm good with a stick.

421
00:50:29,890 --> 00:50:32,080
你知道什么是第戎长炮吗?
Do you know what a Dijon Culverin is?

422
00:50:33,390 --> 00:50:34,050
不知道
No.

423
00:50:34,130 --> 00:50:35,820
是大炮的一种
It's an item of artillery.

424
00:50:35,890 --> 00:50:38,360
你怎么可能解除奥尔良围城之急...
How can you expect to raise the siege of Orleans...

425
00:50:38,370 --> 00:50:41,100
你对现代大炮一无所知
if you're ignorant about modern artillery?

426
00:50:41,110 --> 00:50:45,070
到奥尔良的路还很长 我有优秀副将相伴
The road to Orleans is long, and I have good captains with me.

427
00:50:45,140 --> 00:50:46,830
我会学得很快 相信我
I will learn fast, believe me.

428
00:50:46,900 --> 00:50:50,200
我们很愿意相信你 贞德 但我们觉得...
We would like to believe you, Jeanne, but we feel...

429
00:50:50,270 --> 00:50:53,000
如果上帝要我们相信你...
that if God wanted us to believe you...

430
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:56,410
他就会给你一个神迹
he would've sent a sign with you.

431
00:50:56,480 --> 00:51:00,210
你可以做什么吗?
So, can you do something?

432
00:51:02,450 --> 00:51:04,390
给我们看点什么吧?
Show us something?

433
00:51:05,920 --> 00:51:09,380
这样才能证明...
A sign to prove...

434
00:51:09,460 --> 00:51:11,390
你是上帝派来的
that you are sent by God.

435
00:51:12,900 --> 00:51:16,830
我不是来表演杂耍的
I did not come here to perform tricks.

436
00:51:17,800 --> 00:51:19,060
我...
I...

437
00:51:19,270 --> 00:51:22,330
你们都比我聪明得多
You are all much cleverer than I am.

438
00:51:22,410 --> 00:51:25,840
我是说我大字都不认识一个
I mean, me, I don't know "A" from "B."

439
00:51:25,910 --> 00:51:28,280
但我知道这件事
But this much I do know.

440
00:51:28,350 --> 00:51:32,680
当法国人民血流成河...
While the people of France lie bleeding...

441
00:51:32,750 --> 00:51:34,880
你们还穿着华服坐在这里...
you sit around in your fine clothes...

442
00:51:34,950 --> 00:51:36,980
想欺骗我...
trying to deceive me...

443
00:51:37,050 --> 00:51:40,750
其实你们是在自欺欺人
when you're only deceiving yourselves.

444
00:51:40,820 --> 00:51:43,050
你们自称是上帝的子民...
You say you are men of God...

445
00:51:43,130 --> 00:51:48,060
却看不到他的手引领着我...
yet you do not see His hand in having guided me...

446
00:51:48,130 --> 00:51:53,830
穿过敌国千军万马 为你带来神的帮助
through 500 leagues of enemy country to bring you His help.

447
00:51:53,900 --> 00:51:55,930
这还不能证明吗?
Is that not proof enough?

448
00:52:01,150 --> 00:52:04,080
还是你们需要更多神迹?
Or do you still need more signs?

449
00:52:09,990 --> 00:52:12,110
给我一支军队
Give me an army.

450
00:52:14,490 --> 00:52:17,360
带我到奥尔良
Take me to Orleans.

451
00:52:20,730 --> 00:52:23,600
到时你们就会看到 上帝派我制造的神迹
And there you will see the sign that I was sent to make.

452
00:52:53,590 --> 00:52:54,690
迪努瓦
Dunois.

453
00:52:54,760 --> 00:52:58,560
 什么事?  一颗大的 冲我们来了
 What?  A big one, straight at us.

454
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:02,370
哪一边?
What side?

455
00:53:02,440 --> 00:53:04,300
窗户那边
Window side.

456
00:53:19,820 --> 00:53:20,810
什么事?
What?

457
00:53:22,620 --> 00:53:25,020
终于等到好消息了
I have wonderful news, finally.

458
00:53:25,090 --> 00:53:28,060
他派她过来了 谢天谢地 我们有救了
He is sending her to us. Thanks be to God. We're saved.

459
00:53:28,130 --> 00:53:29,620
真是 真是太好了
It's...It's wonderful.

460
00:53:29,700 --> 00:53:32,670
镇静下 伊特兰斯 说清楚到底什么事?
Calm yourself, Xaintrailles. Who has finally done what?

461
00:53:32,730 --> 00:53:36,130
是皇太子 他给我们送来了粮草和军队...
The dauphin. He's sending us food and supplies and an army...

462
00:53:36,200 --> 00:53:38,930
由贞德率领 那个洛林的女子
led byJeanne, the maiden from Lorraine.

463
00:53:39,010 --> 00:53:41,300
是不是很棒?
Isn't it wonderful?

464
00:53:41,380 --> 00:53:43,310
是啊 简直是奇迹
Yes, it's a miracle.

465
00:53:47,380 --> 00:53:50,250
真不敢相信他们派一个女人过来
I can't believe they are sending a woman.

466
00:53:51,350 --> 00:53:54,120
真想知道她衣服是什么颜色的
I wonder what color dress she'll be wearing.

467
00:53:55,260 --> 00:53:56,480
蓝色
Blue.

468
00:53:57,720 --> 00:54:00,280
头发上还系着蓝丝带 用那个来勒死塔尔博特
With a blue ribbon in her hair to tie up Talbot.

469
00:54:02,830 --> 00:54:06,960
有人知道她到底会骑马吗?
Does anyone know if she even knows how to ride a horse?

470
00:54:07,030 --> 00:54:08,300
看来她会骑
She knows.

471
00:54:22,080 --> 00:54:23,670
你们是迪努瓦大人派来的吗?
Were you sent by Lord Dunois?

472
00:54:23,750 --> 00:54:26,220
是的
Yes, we were.

473
00:54:26,290 --> 00:54:28,980
 英军在哪里?  到处都是 粮草呢?
 Where are the English?  Everywhere. Where's the food?

474
00:54:29,060 --> 00:54:31,750
还在路上 我先赶来了
It's coming. I rode on ahead.

475
00:54:31,830 --> 00:54:34,820
我有消息要告诉英军的将军
I have a message for the captain of the English army.

476
00:54:34,900 --> 00:54:36,360
 他叫塔尔博特  我知道
 His name is Talbot.  I know.

477
00:54:36,430 --> 00:54:40,260
 能带我去见他吗?  他在河对岸
 Can you take me to him?  He's on the other side of the river.

478
00:54:40,330 --> 00:54:43,630
那谁让你带我到这边来的?
So, who gave the order for me to be brought to this side of the river?

479
00:54:44,970 --> 00:54:48,870
老朋友 能再见到你这张老脸还真高兴
Hey, my friend. It's good to see your ugly damn face again.

480
00:54:48,940 --> 00:54:52,170
 拉希尔 我警告过你不要说脏话  对不起 贞德
 La Hire, I'm warning you. Don't swear.  Sorry,Jeanne.

481
00:54:52,250 --> 00:54:56,980
这位是国王的同父异母哥哥迪努瓦大人
Let me introduce the king's half brother, the dogged Lord Dunois.

482
00:54:58,250 --> 00:55:01,400
迪努瓦大人 您能带我去河对岸吗?
Lord Dunois, will you show me to the other side of the river?

483
00:55:01,410 --> 00:55:05,110
等等! 等等!
Wait. Wait!

484
00:55:07,210 --> 00:55:10,570
好啊! 愿意去就去吧! 我可不去
Fine! Go now, if you want! But not with me!

485
00:55:10,580 --> 00:55:14,210
你要对上帝负责 我也要对我的人民负责
You may have a duty to God, but I have a duty to my people.

486
00:55:14,220 --> 00:55:16,880
我的人都快饿死了
And my people are starving.

487
00:55:16,890 --> 00:55:19,780
我要赶紧把粮食运回城去
Right now, I'm going to take the food back to the city.

488
00:55:19,790 --> 00:55:22,980
你镇静些 跟我回奥尔良吧
And if you can please calm down and let me accompany you to Orleans...

489
00:55:22,990 --> 00:55:25,940
很荣幸欢迎你
it will be my honor to welcome you.

490
00:56:24,090 --> 00:56:27,150
主啊
Jesus Christ.

491
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:29,150
该死的英国佬要付出代价的
The goddamn English will pay for this.

492
00:56:29,160 --> 00:56:34,200
是的 他们会遭报应的 可你要再说脏话 你也会的
Yes, they will, and so will you if you don't stop swearing.

493
00:56:51,520 --> 00:56:54,270
进来 欢迎到我的小店来
Come on. I'm happy to welcome you in my tavern.

494
00:56:54,280 --> 00:56:57,020
快进来
Come on in.

495
00:56:58,820 --> 00:57:02,270
拉希尔 吉尔斯 你们过来看看
La Hire, Gilles, let me show you something.

496
00:57:09,800 --> 00:57:14,370
这里是托勒利斯城堡 河从这里穿过
Tourelles are around here. The river crosses there.

497
00:57:17,040 --> 00:57:21,300
冷静下 你不能怪这些人
Calm down. You can't blame those people.

498
00:57:21,310 --> 00:57:22,840
他们几周前就听说你的事了
They've been hearing about you for weeks.

499
00:57:22,850 --> 00:57:26,110
没什么好听的! 知道为什么吗?
There's nothing to hear! And why is there nothing to hear?

500
00:57:26,120 --> 00:57:28,710
因为我还什么都没做 这又是为什么?
Because I haven't done anything! And why haven't I?

501
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:32,060
因为你们没人听我说!
'Cause none of you will listen to me!

502
00:57:36,390 --> 00:57:39,340
你何不过来一起讨论?
Why don't you join us?

503
00:57:39,560 --> 00:57:42,510
我们正在分析军情
We're about to discuss the campaign.

504
00:57:42,900 --> 00:57:45,130
对不起
I'm sorry.

505
00:57:45,140 --> 00:57:47,460
从这里开始 塔尔博特在这些堡垒间
So from here, Talbot has spread his forces...

506
00:57:47,470 --> 00:57:49,630
都布置了他的部队
between these forts up here.

507
00:57:49,640 --> 00:57:52,170
据我们侦查 过去几天里...
But in the last few days it seems, according to our scouts...

508
00:57:52,180 --> 00:57:54,870
在这个堡垒处聚集了一些部队
that some troops have been deployed to this fort here.

509
00:57:54,880 --> 00:57:56,740
这个大家伙是什么?
What about this huge pile down here?

510
00:57:56,750 --> 00:57:58,810
那就是托勒利斯城堡 英国人准备以它为基地开展进攻
That's the Tourelles. The English were planning...

511
00:57:58,820 --> 00:58:01,980
于是我们就把桥拆了
to launch an attack from it, but then we broke down the bridge...

512
00:58:01,990 --> 00:58:04,850
 是我干的  是的
 I did.  Yeah.

513
00:58:04,860 --> 00:58:06,850
这样一来他们会安静一阵子
Which should keep them quiet for a while.

514
00:58:06,860 --> 00:58:09,850
我的预感是...
Now, my hunch is...

515
00:58:09,860 --> 00:58:12,420
他们会从圣鲁普发动进攻
the attack will come from St. Loup, here.

516
00:58:12,430 --> 00:58:15,760
贞德 你有什么看法呢?
And what does Jeanne think?

517
00:58:15,770 --> 00:58:19,530
我没有看法 那是上帝的事情
I don't think. I leave that to God.

518
00:58:19,540 --> 00:58:22,700
我不管这些 我只负责传达音讯
I am nothing in all of this. I'm just the messenger.

519
00:58:22,710 --> 00:58:24,330
那么...
So...

520
00:58:24,340 --> 00:58:26,330
音讯是什么呢?
what is the message?

521
00:58:26,340 --> 00:58:29,870
我们给英国人...
We give the English...

522
00:58:29,880 --> 00:58:32,470
最后一次机会让他们和平撤军
a last chance to go home in peace.

523
00:58:32,480 --> 00:58:34,040
如果他们拒绝呢?
And if they refuse?

524
00:58:34,050 --> 00:58:36,650
如果他们拒绝...
If they refuse...

525
00:58:38,020 --> 00:58:41,090
我们就渡过河...
we recross the river...

526
00:58:41,320 --> 00:58:44,050
攻击这里...
and attack here...

527
00:58:44,060 --> 00:58:46,470
攻击托勒利斯
at the Tourelles.

528
